    "updated_at": "2015-10-21T09:38:54Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Our convention for a long time has been that any times related to the world state must be defined in ticks (and with the new game speeds, should not be scaled).  Only UI related things (such as delays between sound notifications, etc) should be defined in seconds, and these should all be scaled.\n\nGiven this, I propose a more accurate title: world simulation times should be converted to ticks.  We may actually have a ticket for this.\n"
  },
