    "updated_at": "2015-10-21T15:14:33Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "From what I understood. We don't need to replace them with raw tick values, as\n`DateTime.Seconds(x)` just returns `x * 25`, `DateTime.Minutes(x)` returns `DateTime.Seconds(x) * 60`,\nso they actually just return ticks...\n\nI think the problem at the moment (with the lua timers) is, that `Utils.FormatTime` `WidgetUtils.FormatTime` calls which cares about different game speeds (`<+pchote> things that actually do care about real-time seconds (such as delays between UI effects) should account for the game speed`).\n"
  },
